Directives are essentially a way for us to create our 
HTML elements that act like built in elements

Directives:
  we can use angular directives
  e.g. use ng-switch to show different vizs

  <div ng-switch on="selection">
    <div ng-switch-when="pie">
      <pie-chart></pie-chart>
    </div>
    <div ng-switch-default>
      <bar-chart></bar-chart>
    </div>

<div ng-repeat="races in incomes">
  <map ng-repeat="race in races"></map>
</div>